[30;1m36 | [0m[35m    connection instances. In init time it is passed a dictionary containing all[0m
[30;1m37 | [0m[35m    the connections' options which it can then use during the selection[0m
[30;1m38 | [0m[35m    process. When the `select` method is called it is given a list of[0m
[30;1m39 | [0m[35m    *currently* live connections to choose from.[0m

   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m# - If we use 'type: ignore' on 'import aiohttp' and it's not installed[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m#   mypy will complain that the annotation is unnecessary.[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m# - If we don't use 'type: ignore' on 'import aiohttp' and it[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35m#   it's not installed mypy will complain that it can't find[0m
[30;1m27 | [0m[35m#   type hints for aiohttp.[0m
[30;1m28 | [0m[35m# So to make mypy happy we move all our 'extra' imports here[0m
[30;1m29 | [0m[35m# and add a global 'type: ignore' which mypy never complains[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35m# about being unnecessary.[0m
